> [{quoted}](name=Riot ShadowStorm,realm=NA,application-id=6kFXY1kR,discussion-id=GxMOI0BV,comment-id=0000000000010010000000040000,timestamp=2015-10-22T00:15:37.100+0000)
>
> I was just using the terms that ItemsGuy used, to help distinguish how a character might exist/be perceived in Runeterra. I don't think there's a major difference "in Riot's eyes" here, but having the different terms is nice for helping to see more of what you're all looking for!

I see it this way: champion or legend doesn't really have to do with powers or abilities. From my perspective, a champion is someone who has a life to live, while a legend is more... one-dimensional isn't the right word... I guess more apart from the world.

So, a list of champions would be: {{champion:22}} {{champion:51}} {{champion:42}}  {{champion:131}} {{champion:36}}   {{champion:4}} {{champion:99}} {{champion:245}} {{champion:74}} 

While legends would be more like: {{champion:266}}  {{champion:432}} {{champion:9}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:82}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:26}}{{champion:10}}{{champion:25}} 

I guess that means I sort of think there is a third category too... Something more like "marvels" that fit in between champions and legends, like:
{{champion:103}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:32}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:96}} {{champion:107}} {{champion:127}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:72}} {{champion:421}} 
just to name a few.
